headline: SpaceX Could Be Worth as Much as Tesla. How Musk Manufactures Trillion Dollar Companies.
summary: Like him or not, it’s hard to dispute that Elon Musk generates some incredible numbers.  Take SpaceX.  Earlier in the week, Musk appeared to confirm that SpaceX was on track for a 2026 IPO, which would provide capital to accelerate AI data centers in space and value SpaceX at up to $1.5 trillion.

headline: Boeing, GE, and 10 More Stocks to Play Aerospace & Defense ‘Megatrends’
summary: Citi  has a new aerospace and defense analyst.  The sector is “at the center of a number of megatrends—secular, multi-year growth drivers largely not dependent on the economy,” wrote Citi analyst John Godyn.  Trends include: rising demand for air travel, increasing commercial jet production, international rearmament, AI-trained drone and missile technology, and the rise of a space economy.
